<TITLE> 3 women, NGO win Citi entrepreneur prize </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com)  Three women entrepreneurs and a non-government organisation were the recipients of the 'Citi Micro Entrepreneurship Awards 2008' on Thursday. Finance adviser ABM Azizul Islam handed over the awards at a ceremony organised by the Citi Foundation at Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre in the city. Sabrina Begum of Gazipur received the 'best micro entrepreneur' award for her success in fashioning baseball caps from garment factory leftovers. 'Best woman micro entrepreneur' award went to Baby Chakma, from Rangamati, for dairy farming and by-products from cow dung. Salma Akter Sahida of Pabna received the 'best creative micro entrepreneur' award for developing weaving toolstraditionally wooden-madeout of recycled plastic and polythene. The Society for Social Service, a Tangail-based NGO, received the 'best micro credit programme' award. The award ceremony was attended by Citi Bank country officer and MD Mamun Rashid, Shakti Foundation executive director Humaira Islam and economist Wahiduddin Mahmud, among others. City Foundation is part of Citigroup Inc. bdnews2
